# FastAPI Standards

## Purpose
Define minimal FastAPI conventions for this project.

## Rules
- Keep `app/main.py` small: app creation, router registration, metadata, and health endpoint.
- Put API routes in `app/routers/`.
- Use Pydantic models for request and response schemas.
- Use dependency injection for settings and services when it improves testability.
- Do not instantiate provider clients directly inside route handlers.
- Route handlers should orchestrate, not contain business logic.
- Use clear HTTP status codes and safe user-facing error messages.
- Keep API versioning explicit with `/api/v1`.

## Initial Layout
```text
app/
├── main.py
├── config.py
├── routers/
│   └── estimations.py
├── services/
│   └── llm_service.py
└── context/
    └── examples.py
```

## Runtime Commands
- Run locally with `uv run uvicorn app.main:app --reload`.
- Keep runtime commands documented in `README.md`.

## Checklist
- [ ] Routes call services, not provider SDKs directly.
- [ ] Request and response schemas are explicit.
- [ ] Settings are loaded through `pydantic-settings`.
- [ ] API errors do not expose secrets or internal stack traces.
- [ ] Swagger remains available at `/docs`.

